The paper deals with the problem of learning from untrusted batches, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of statistical learning theory. The paper also discusses the use of semidefinite programming and Haar wavelets, which are commonly used in optimization and signal processing, respectively. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Signal Processing), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
